<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[138,778,980,1703]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055">
Pileus 
<quantity box="[201,308,980,1000]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" unit="mm" value="65.0" valueMax="80.0" valueMin="50.0">50–80 mm</quantity>
, hemispherical then plano-convex, glabrous, glutinous, uniformly pale to darker brown (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[586,607,1011,1030]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055">̿</emphasis>
4B5 to 4C7–6D6), margin paler cream–brown to yellow–brown, sometimes with pale to violaceous universal veil remnants especially on margin. Lamellae emarginate,pale violaceous (15–17A2 to paler).Stipe 35– 
<date box="[138,242,1133,1153]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" value="1955-10-10" valueMax="1955-10-15" valueMin="1955-10-10">
55 X 
<quantity box="[186,291,1133,1153]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" unit="mm" value="12.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="10.0">10–15 mm</quantity>
</date>
with an often not so wide bulb (– 
<quantity box="[631,707,1133,1153]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 mm</quantity>
), often intensely violaceous (17–18A3–19A4), but often paler (
<emphasis bold="true" box="[693,714,1164,1183]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055">̿</emphasis>
17A2). The colour is very consistent and persistent, though it fades from below with age and often discolours brownish. Bulb often sharply marginate,though not so wide, bulbipellis and mycelial strands whitish, bulb margin on younger specimens sometimes with remnants of violaceous veil.Cortina violaceous.Veil pale to faintly violaceus. Context whitish, in stipe cortex violaceous. Taste mild, smell indistinct. Spores amygdaliform to citriform with broad long apex, with distinct coarse ornament, relatively dark in the microscope, 
<date box="[380,457,1438,1458]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" value="1910-10-11">10–11 X</date>
<quantity box="[462,570,1438,1458]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="5.5">5.5–6.5 µm</quantity>
, average 10.4 ± 0.4 X 6.1 ± 
<quantity box="[192,261,1469,1489]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 µm</quantity>
; Q ¼ 1.72 ± 0.08.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[138,778,980,1703]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055">Chemical reactions: KOH on pileipellis almost negative to brownish (6F7) but not red, on bulbipellis negative, in context negative or weak rose.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="9.[138,778,980,1703]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055">Habitat: Known from frondose forests with Fagus and Quercus on calcareous to mineral rich soil, but has also been found in mixed forests with Carpinus betulus, Q. petraea, Q. cerris and Tilia tomentosa.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[824,1463,178,1683]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055">
Observations/Discussion: Among calochroid taxa, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vesterholtii">C. vesterholtii</taxonomicName>
is easily recognised by the brown pileus colours, the violet stipe, and the negative alkaline reaction on the bulbipellis. Similar species have lighter or livelier colours on the pileus, and/or a pink alkaline reaction on the bulbipellis. The most obvious possibility of misidentification is discoloured specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rob. Henry" authorityYear="1935" box="[980,1115,362,382]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sodagnitus">C. sodagnitus</taxonomicName>
and possibly 
<taxonomicName authorityName="in Quercus" box="[1276,1455,362,382]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="parasuaveolens">C. parasuaveolens</taxonomicName>
, both having positive alkaline reactions. Furthermore, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vesterholtii">C. vesterholtii</taxonomicName>
has some morphological affinities to distantly related non-calochroid species such as 
<taxonomicName box="[1163,1318,453,473]" class="Polycystina" family="Stephaniidae" genus="Cortina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="species" species="purpurascens">C. purpurascens</taxonomicName>
, which differ by the typical purple staining reaction of species in that group. Superficial resemblance with brownish stained specimens belonging to the C. coerulescens group is also a possibility. These, however, have spores without a net-like ornamentation, and have a well-differentiated hypodermal layer, not seen in any calochroid taxa, and pronounced innate fibrils in the pileus. Furthermore, the violaceous colours of the stipe and lamellae of these species are more bluish than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vesterholtii">C. vesterholtii</taxonomicName>
. The species has been treated under the name 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moser" baseAuthorityYear="1997" class="Polycystina" family="Stephaniidae" genus="Cortina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="species" species="provencalis">C. provencalis</taxonomicName>
(e.g. 
<bibRefCitation author="Bidaud A &amp; Moenne-Loccoz P &amp; Reumaux P &amp; Carteret X &amp; Eyssartier G" box="[924,1112,759,779]" journalOrPublisher="Phlegmacium sect. Calochroi." pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" refId="ref13602" refString="Bidaud A, Moenne-Loccoz P, Reumaux P, Carteret X, Eyssartier G, 2001. Atlas des Cortinaires XI (2) Phlegmacium sect. Calochroi. Editions Federation mycologique Dauphine-Savoie, Lyon." title="Atlas des Cortinaires" type="book" year="2001">Bidaud et al. 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Moser MM" box="[1123,1242,759,779]" journalOrPublisher="Micologia e Vegetazione Mediterranea" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" pagination="121 - 135" part="12" refId="ref14105" refString="Moser MM, 1997. Notes on some Mediterranean Cortinarii. Micologia e Vegetazione Mediterranea 12: 121 - 135." title="Notes on some Mediterranean Cortinarii" type="journal article" year="1997">Moser 1997</bibRefCitation>
). Moser’s concept of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moser" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[824,981,789,809]" class="Polycystina" family="Stephaniidae" genus="Cortina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="species" species="provencalis">C. provencalis</taxonomicName>
included (discoloured) collections of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rob. Henry" authorityYear="1935" box="[824,956,820,840]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sodagnitus">C. sodagnitus</taxonomicName>
along with the present species. The collection published in 
<bibRefCitation author="Moser MM &amp; Julich W" box="[956,1163,850,871]" journalOrPublisher="Gustav Fisher Verlag, Stuttgart" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" refId="ref14126" refString="Moser MM, Julich W, 1985 - 1999. Farbatlas der Basidiomyceten, Vol. 1 - 17, Gustav Fisher Verlag, Stuttgart." title="Farbatlas der Basidiomyceten, Vol. 1" type="book" year="1985">
Moser &amp; Jülich (
<date box="[1114,1221,850,870]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" value="1985" valueMax="1999">1985–1999</date>
</bibRefCitation>
) as C. coeruleoochrascens almost certainly represents 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" box="[1121,1254,881,901]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vesterholtii">C. vesterholtii</taxonomicName>
, a collection Moser referred to when describing 
<taxonomicName authority="(Moser 1997)" authorityName="Moser" authorityYear="1997" baseAuthorityName="Moser" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1129,1409,912,932]" class="Polycystina" family="Stephaniidae" genus="Cortina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="species" species="provencalis">
C. provencalis (
<bibRefCitation author="Moser MM" box="[1281,1400,912,932]" journalOrPublisher="Micologia e Vegetazione Mediterranea" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" pagination="121 - 135" part="12" refId="ref14105" refString="Moser MM, 1997. Notes on some Mediterranean Cortinarii. Micologia e Vegetazione Mediterranea 12: 121 - 135." title="Notes on some Mediterranean Cortinarii" type="journal article" year="1997">Moser 1997</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The type of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moser" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[914,1054,942,962]" class="Polycystina" family="Stephaniidae" genus="Cortina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="species" species="provencalis">C. provencalis</taxonomicName>
, however, represents a collection of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rob. Henry" authorityYear="1935" box="[824,952,973,993]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sodagnitus">C. sodagnitus</taxonomicName>
(Frøslev et al., unpublished) leaving 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moser" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1329,1462,973,993]" class="Polycystina" family="Stephaniidae" genus="Cortina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="species" species="provencalis">C. provencalis</taxonomicName>
a synonym of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rob. Henry" authorityYear="1935" box="[990,1125,1003,1023]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sodagnitus">C. sodagnitus</taxonomicName>
. This also explains the larger variability of alkaline reactions and some morphological characters in the protologue of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moser" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1142,1282,1064,1084]" class="Polycystina" family="Stephaniidae" genus="Cortina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="species" species="provencalis">C. provencalis</taxonomicName>
compared with the variability observed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Rob. Henry" authorityYear="1935" box="[1105,1234,1095,1115]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sodagnitus">C. sodagnitus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" box="[1287,1423,1095,1115]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vesterholtii">C. vesterholtii</taxonomicName>
, respectively. The species is named after the Danish mycologist, Jan Vesterholt, who urged us to continue our study of this interesting group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S.F.Gray" authorityYear="1821" baseAuthorityName="Person" box="[1025,1132,1186,1206]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Cortinarius</taxonomicName>
. We have seen several photographs and references to this species (as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Moser" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1262,1396,1217,1237]" class="Polycystina" family="Stephaniidae" genus="Cortina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Chromista" order="Nassellaria" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Radiozoa" rank="species" species="provencalis">C. provencalis</taxonomicName>
) from the Mediterranean area, and it is most likely widespread, but not common in this area, whereas the species seems to be very rare in Northern Europe. An ITS sequence from the 
<typeStatus pageId="9" pageNumber="1055">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" box="[919,1058,1339,1359]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="vesterholtii">C. vesterholtii</taxonomicName>
is available at GenBank (accession 
<accessionNumber box="[824,926,1370,1390]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/DQ350842" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055">
<collectionCode box="[824,854,1370,1390]" pageId="9" pageNumber="1055">DQ</collectionCode>
350842
</accessionNumber>
).
</paragraph>
